<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>In Cotton the world had fallen into an endless night after an evil Demoness called Wool stole the 7 Willows that brought light to it. In desperation, the Fairy Queen Velvet dispatched a beautiful fairy named Silk to get the Willows back. Before long, Silk met up with Cotton, a witch who loved to eat Willows, and together, they defeated Wool and brought back the willows. Light returned to the world, and Cotton left on her own.
                  <br><br>The Playstation version of the game have a new feature that is the vibration function.
                  <br><br>Block Keeper is a puzzle game in which 2 players can play in a cooperative mode.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Set in the world of magic, horizontal scrolling shooter will defeat the enemy with shot and magic. I can select a favorite from among the four groups magic is possible. Cotton witch girl that journey Find WILLOW favorite, would have been branded as a villain in a fairy silk gave help before. Whether it is possible to dispel the frame-up is really cotton! ?
                  <br><br>Three in the same pattern, we will turn off or side-by-side in the same three colors, a lithograph that appears in the mass of 5 × 5. Game over trout After all filled with lithograph. High scores of both pattern and color or were together, and when you put it out once more lithograph. It is possible two cooperative play, also 2 player game play.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Fantasy theme.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

